item.title: Java Decompiler?
item.dc:creator: @T41 t4
item.description:
@T41 wrote:

[quote=“veer, post:7, topic:444697”][quote author=Disorder link=topic=547384.msg4013721#msg4013721 date=1339449247]

There are programs that convert the files in a more readable format. E.G. int a = int anInt1 and Client b = aClient1, and so forth.

Would it output ‘Hour anHour1’ instead of ‘Hour a’? Probably not. There’s still room for these renamers to improve, aHour1 would be bad.
[/quote]

ZKM would emit ‘aHour1’ instead of ‘Hour a’, which is close.
AFAIK, no Java renamers attempt linguistic analysis on code to identify morphemes in name and thus decide whether to use ‘a’ vs ‘an’.[/quote]
@Disorder holy fuck, who cares about ‘a’ vs ‘an’

Read full topic
